<br>
You are also able to run in with 60 warrior, take the first AE, call everyone else in, anyone 4k or higher in hps will live till the third AE assuming no healing = 17 secs on first 2k dmg + 18 secs on next 2k dmg + 18 secs on next DEAD...<br>
<br>
So at least your melee live to 50ish seconds with no healing, Casters maybe one more and Melee maybe two more if all healers are on the ball.<br>
<br>
Ok, I got all that.<br>
<br>
Now let's talk about something else.<br>
<br>
I have soloed (the only melee fighting that is) Lord Rak Ashiir in City of Mist twice in the last 3 weeks. I put a nice decent sized 70-80 point damage shield on. First try I had a cleric and three druids and second try I had two shamans and two druids.<br>
<br>
Neither fight came close in terms of mana.<br>
<br>
I can just get to 6k hps if I have BMB Aego and 60 Shaman Buffs.<br>
<br>
I have a non-kos mage that is willing to come with us on Sunday to park the queen away from her guards and keep her hailed.<br>
<br>
With a full raid (8-10 healers with Cheal or almost Cheal+ another 8-10 with spam heals+runes) isn't it very possible that I could just run up engage, have people heal me and let my damage and the Damage shield do the work down to 40% and then have people rush her at 8.8k hps instead of 22?<br>
<br>
My alliance can do HoT and keep people alive in the face of 300 and 400 pt AE's but I am not sure we are organized enough to keep 30 people alive to a 2000 pt AE every 18 seconds. We are, however, very practiced at keeping my Warrior alive (I am the MA for the alliance)<br>
<br>
Thoughts? Giant Holes in Analysis? Overall Comments?<br>
<br>
Please try to think of this with the last paragraph in mind, people who have done this before and/or lay waste to NToV on a regular basis may not have the perspective I need if they don't. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Thanks a bunch for listening and I welcome your responses.<br>
<br>
Jakle<br>
